metrics_conclusion: In terms of chords and melody, Viva Las Vengeance is significantly more complex than the typical song, having above average scores in Chord Complexity, Melodic Complexity, Chord-Melody Tension, Chord Progression Novelty and Chord-Bass Melody.
key_conclusion: Viva Las Vengeance has sections analyzed in the following keys: D Major,  and D Minor.  Click on the linked cheat sheets for popular chords, chord progressions, downloadable midi files and more!

metadata.editComments: Corrected the rhythm for the last phrase of the melody, like I said I would. This makes more sense and feels more even to me.

Added triplets where they were notated in the official sheet music. Added a Bbm (maj7) based on the vocal harmonies, which is borrowed from F Phrygian Dominant. But I changed the key of this section as a whole to D minor because there's a Dm (maj7) chord in the sheet music which needed to be added here, so that must be harmonic minor. I also changed the Gsus4 chord to G add11 because while the guitar part is playing a C, the vocal harmonies still include a B natural. Fixed the sync start time.
